data.sampled: If you don't have your phone with you, you can use a feature called "Text for Help" to get in touch with customer support. You can also use this feature if you accidentally lost your account number or password. To use Text for Help, simply text the word "HELP" to 30111. A representative will then be able to assist you with any questions you have. Alternatively, you can visit a TD Canada Trust branch or a TD ATM where you can seek assistance in person.

data.sampled: The exchange rate for a foreign ATM is different than the exchange rate for card transactions or bank transfers in some cases due to the fact that when you withdraw cash from an ATM, the bank that issued your card or the bank that owns the ATM you are using may charge additional fees, including an "international transaction fee" or "foreign transaction fee" which is added to the exchange rate for the transaction. This fee can vary depending on the bank or card issuer, as well as the country you are withdrawing cash in. It is important to check with your bank or card issuer for the exact fees and exchange rates they charge for foreign ATM withdrawals.
